name: Knorr Student Center
directions: In the basement in the media department, which is not clearly labeled at all but it's the next door down after you pass Career Services and the Writing Center, there is one unisex bathroom. When you go into the media department, you'll want to turn right and head back, go down the hallway to your right, and the bathroom is all the way at the end on your left. Inconvenient and hard to find, but handy, especially if you work in the media department.

name: Wisconsin Institute For Medical Research
directions: Floors 3 for sure has two restrooms near the staircase, other floors above that are likely similar. If you take the elevator, make sure to select your floor with the touchscreens in the area. They'll indicate which elevator you should get in. Once you get off the elevator, take a left and go down to the end of the hall. The stairs entrance is right next to the two restrooms. Very clean!
comment: The building is full of research labs and meeting rooms, so make sure to be quiets. Otherwise, the halls are relatively deserted.
